  "prompt": "How can we define UPSC?",
  "response": "UPSC stands for the Union Public Service Commission, which is a constitutional body in India responsible for recruiting candidates for various civil services and posts in the government. Here are some key points about UPSC:\n\n1. Constitutional Body:\n- Established under Article 315 of the Indian Constitution\n- Plays a crucial role in the recruitment of government officers\n\n2. Main Functions:\n- Conducting civil services examinations\n- Recruiting candidates for prestigious services like IAS, IPS, IFS\n- Recommending candidates for central government positions\n- Conducting interviews and personality tests\n\n3. Examination Process:\n- Preliminary Examination\n- Main Examination\n- Personality Test/Interview\n- Considered one of the most competitive exams in India\n\n4. Services Covered:\n- Indian Administrative Service (IAS)\n- Indian Police Service (IPS)\n- Indian Foreign Service (IFS)\n- Other Group A and Group B services\n\n5. Independence:\n- Autonomous body\n- Works independently of government interference\n- Ensures fair and merit-based selection\n\n6. Significance:\n- Considered the premier recruiting agency for civil services\n- Plays a crucial role in selecting administrative leadership\n- Ensures quality recruitment for government positions",
